    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Per-module service economics</h2>
    <p>LA Gaggenau kitchens typically run 3-5 modules in the wall-oven column. When service is needed, the failure concentrates in specific modules rather than taking out the whole column — one module's control board fails while others work fine, or one module's heating element burns out independently. Service dispatch economics favor handling multiple modules in one visit when the failure mix allows:</p>
    <p><b>Single-module service call</b> — diagnostic + repair on one module. Typical call covers $400-$900 range for routine single-component work on one module.</p>
    <p><b>Multi-module service call</b> — two or more modules needing service on the same dispatch. Combined diagnostic efficiency + shared travel time keeps the combined visit more economical than two separate appointments. Typical combined $700-$1,600 depending on module mix.</p>
    <p><b>Full-column preventive check</b> — operator requesting proactive inspection across all modules. Not a standard service offering but we accommodate on request for high-use Gaggenau households; diagnostic time + component verification across 4-5 modules runs $300-$500.</p>
    <p>When we dispatch a Gaggenau call, we ask about the whole column — sometimes a module the operator hadn't flagged as problematic turns out to have a developing issue worth inspecting on the same visit.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common Gaggenau wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>400 Series BO bake element failure</b> — heavy-duty element lasts 10-14 years typical. Replacement $480-$780.</p>
    <p><b>BO convection fan motor</b> — bearings develop play. Replacement $520-$840.</p>
    <p><b>400 Series BO control board firmware lockout</b> — factory reset sometimes resolves; replacement $680-$1,080 when not.</p>
    <p><b>BS combi-steam descale overdue</b> — LA hard-water scale on boiler + plumbing. Service $280-$460. Annual cadence recommended.</p>
    <p><b>BS boiler element burnout</b> — deferred descale consequence. Replacement $540-$880.</p>
    <p><b>BS steam-distribution valve</b> — electromechanical valve failure. Replacement $380-$640.</p>
    <p><b>BM speed oven magnetron service</b> — microwave-side component. $440-$720.</p>
    <p><b>BMP warming drawer element</b> — low-temp element eventually fails. Replacement $380-$640.</p>
    <p><b>Module-specific temperature sensor drift</b> — each module has its own sensor. Replacement $340-$540 per module.</p>
    <p><b>Door hinges across modules</b> — Gaggenau hinges hold up well but develop play over decade-plus service life. Replacement $380-$620.</p>
  </div></section>

